Package: metaoverfit
Type: Package
Title: Optimism-Corrected Heterogeneity in Meta-Regression
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Mahmood", family = "Ahmad", email = "mahmood.ahmad2@nhs.net", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person(given = "Laiba", family = "Khan", email = "drlaiba999@gmail.com", role = "aut"))
Description: Implements cross-validation methods to detect and correct for overfitting in meta-regression. 
    Provides optimism-corrected R-squared measures, bootstrap confidence intervals, and diagnostic tools 
    for assessing the reliability of heterogeneity explanations in meta-analysis. Methods are based on 
    the optimism correction framework described by Harrell et al. (1996) <doi:10.1002/(SICI)1097-0258(19960229)15:4<361::AID-SIM168>3.0.CO;2-4> 
    and cross-validation approaches for meta-analysis discussed by Higgins and Thompson (2002) <doi:10.1002/sim.1186>.
